    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-18T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12895: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-18T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 18, 1934—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 18—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>583. Reference Legation’s 581, December 18, 3 p.m. Following has been received
                    from Peck at Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 18, 11 a.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>In response to my request that naval vessel be sent to Wuhu <hi
                                    rend="italic">Panay</hi> left Nanking December 18, 6 a.m. No
                                American vessel here now.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>All American citizens in southern Anhwei now reported to be in
                                Wuhu with possible exception of Olson family at Tatung on the
                                Yangtze.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>I have telephoned to the Foreign Office substance of my radio
                                message to commander of the Yangtze patrol of December 17, 11 p.m.
                                which was repeated to the Legation and have asked for confirmation
                                thereof and for information concerning measures taken to meet
                                possible emergency at Wuhu.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
